{
  "apiVersion": "dashboard.grafana.app/v1",
  "kind": "Dashboard",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "tuist-kura-rollout",
    "annotations": {
      "grafana.app/folder": "tuist"
    }
  },
  "spec": {
    "title": "Tuist Kura Rollout",
    "uid": "tuist-kura-rollout",
    "description": "Health-gated progressive rollout of Kura runtime versions (spec #79). Control-plane rollout state (PromEx, tuist_kura_rollout_*) joined with the per-node gate signals (outbox depth, file-descriptor pressure, peer-connection failures, memory pressure), so a pause is explainable from this dashboard alone: which wave stopped, which server held it, and which signal regressed.",
    "schemaVersion": 39,
    "refresh": "30s",
    "tags": ["tuist", "kura", "rollout"],
    "time": {
      "from": "now-6h",
      "to": "now"
    },
    "templating": {
      "list": [
        {
          "current": {
            "selected": false,
            "text": "grafanacloud-prom",
            "value": "grafanacloud-prom"
          },
          "hide": 0,
          "includeAll": false,
          "label": "Data Source",
          "multi": false,
          "name": "datasource",
          "options": [],
          "query": "prometheus",
          "refresh": 1,
          "regex": "",
          "skipUrlSync": false,
          "type": "datasource"
        },
        {
          "current": {
            "selected": true,
            "text": "production",
            "value": "production"
          },
          "hide": 0,
          "includeAll": false,
          "label": "Environment",
          "multi": false,
          "name": "env",
          "options": [
            {
              "selected": true,
              "text": "production",
              "value": "production"
            },
            {
              "selected": false,
              "text": "canary",
              "value": "canary"
            },
            {
              "selected": false,
              "text": "staging",
              "value": "staging"
            }
          ],
          "query": "production,canary,staging",
          "queryValue": "",
          "skipUrlSync": false,
          "type": "custom"
        }
      ]
    },
    "panels": [
      {
        "collapsed": false,
        "gridPos": { "h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 0 },
        "id": 100,
        "panels": [],
        "title": "Rollout",
        "type": "row"
      },
      {
        "datasource": "$datasource",
        "description": "The rollout's target image tag while a rollout is running or paused. Empty when the fleet is idle.",
        "fieldConfig": {
          "defaults": {
            "color": { "mode": "thresholds" },
            "thresholds": {
              "mode": "absolute",
              "steps": [{ "color": "blue", "value": null }]
            },
            "unit": "short"
          }
        },
        "gridPos": { "h": 4, "w": 6, "x": 0, "y": 1 },
        "id": 110,
        "options": {
          "colorMode": "background",
          "graphMode": "none",
          "justifyMode": "center",
          "orientation": "horizontal",
          "reduceOptions": {
            "calcs": ["lastNotNull"],
            "fields": "",
            "values": false
          },
          "textMode": "name"
        },
        "targets": [
          {
            "datasource": "$datasource",
            "editorMode": "code",
            "expr": "max by (image_tag, mode) (tuist_kura_rollout_active{env=\"$env\"} == 1)",
            "instant": true,
            "legendFormat": "{{image_tag}} ({{mode}})",
            "refId": "A"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Active rollout",
        "type": "stat"
      },
      {
        "datasource": "$datasource",
        "description": "1 while the rollout is paused. A pause means the gate stopped a wave (or an operator did); the rollout schedules nothing further until resumed, expedited, aborted, or superseded.",
        "fieldConfig": {
          "defaults": {
            "color": { "mode": "thresholds" },
            "thresholds": {
              "mode": "absolute",
              "steps": [
                { "color": "green", "value": null },
                { "color": "red", "value": 1 }
              ]
            },
            "unit": "short"
          }
        },
        "gridPos": { "h": 4, "w": 4, "x": 6, "y": 1 },
        "id": 111,
        "options": {
          "colorMode": "background",
          "graphMode": "none",
          "justifyMode": "center",
          "orientation": "horizontal",
          "reduceOptions": {
            "calcs": ["lastNotNull"],
            "fields": "",
            "values": false
          },
          "textMode": "auto"
        },
        "targets": [
          {
            "datasource": "$datasource",
            "editorMode": "code",
            "expr": "max(tuist_kura_rollout_paused{env=\"$env\"})",
            "instant": true,
            "refId": "A"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Paused",
        "type": "stat"
      },
      {
        "datasource": "$datasource",
        "description": "Current wave of the active rollout. Wave 0 is the Tuist-owned canary; waves 1-3 split the customer accounts by recent usage ascending.",
        "fieldConfig": {
          "defaults": {
            "color": { "mode": "thresholds" },
            "thresholds": {
              "mode": "absolute",
              "steps": [{ "color": "blue", "value": null }]
            },
            "unit": "short"
          }
        },
        "gridPos": { "h": 4, "w": 4, "x": 10, "y": 1 },
        "id": 112,
        "options": {
          "colorMode": "value",
          "graphMode": "none",
          "justifyMode": "center",
          "orientation": "horizontal",
          "reduceOptions": {
            "calcs": ["lastNotNull"],
            "fields": "",
            "values": false
          },
          "textMode": "auto"
        },
        "targets": [
          {
            "datasource": "$datasource",
            "editorMode": "code",
            "expr": "max(tuist_kura_rollout_wave{env=\"$env\"} and on () (max(tuist_kura_rollout_active{env=\"$env\"}) == 1))",
            "instant": true,
            "refId": "A"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Current wave",
        "type": "stat"
      },
      {
        "datasource": "$datasource",
        "description": "Seconds since the current wave opened. The wave deadline pauses the rollout at 60 minutes without completion.",
        "fieldConfig": {
          "defaults": {
            "color": { "mode": "thresholds" },
            "thresholds": {
              "mode": "absolute",
              "steps": [
                { "color": "green", "value": null },
                { "color": "yellow", "value": 1800 },
                { "color": "red", "value": 3600 }
              ]
            },
            "unit": "s"
          }
        },
        "gridPos": { "h": 4, "w": 4, "x": 14, "y": 1 },
        "id": 113,
        "options": {
          "colorMode": "background",
          "graphMode": "area",
          "justifyMode": "center",
          "orientation": "horizontal",
          "reduceOptions": {
            "calcs": ["lastNotNull"],
            "fields": "",
            "values": false
          },
          "textMode": "auto"
        },
        "targets": [
          {
            "datasource": "$datasource",
            "editorMode": "code",
            "expr": "max(tuist_kura_rollout_wave_age_seconds{env=\"$env\"})",
            "instant": true,
            "refId": "A"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Wave age",
        "type": "stat"
      },
      {
        "datasource": "$datasource",
        "description": "Servers scoped into the rollout so far versus servers observed on the target image. One row per server; instance replicas are not double-counted.",
        "fieldConfig": {
          "defaults": {
            "color": { "mode": "palette-classic" },
            "custom": {
              "drawStyle": "line",
              "fillOpacity": 10,
              "lineWidth": 2,
              "showPoints": "never"
            },
            "unit": "short"
          }
        },
        "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 6, "x": 18, "y": 1 },
        "id": 114,
        "options": {
          "legend": {
            "displayMode": "list",
            "placement": "bottom",
            "showLegend": true
          },
          "tooltip": { "mode": "multi", "sort": "none" }
        },
        "targets": [
          {
            "datasource": "$datasource",
            "editorMode": "code",
            "expr": "max(tuist_kura_rollout_servers_scoped{env=\"$env\"})",
            "legendFormat": "scoped",
            "refId": "A"
          },
          {
            "datasource": "$datasource",
            "editorMode": "code",
            "expr": "max(tuist_kura_rollout_servers_converged{env=\"$env\"})",
            "legendFormat": "converged",
            "refId": "B"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Converged vs scoped servers",
        "type": "timeseries"
      },
      {
        "collapsed": false,
        "gridPos": { "h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 9 },
        "id": 200,
        "panels": [],
        "title": "Fleet convergence",
        "type": "row"
      },
      {
        "datasource": "$datasource",
        "description": "Non-destroyed Kura servers per observed image tag. A rollout reads as one tag's series draining into another; a stall reads as the curve flattening mid-crossover.",
        "fieldConfig": {
          "defaults": {
            "color": { "mode": "palette-classic" },
            "custom": {
              "drawStyle": "line",
              "fillOpacity": 40,
              "lineWidth": 1,
              "showPoints": "never",
              "stacking": { "group": "A", "mode": "normal" }
            },
            "unit": "short"
          }
        },
        "gridPos": { "h": 9, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 10 },
        "id": 210,
        "options": {
          "legend": {
            "displayMode": "table",
            "placement": "right",
            "showLegend": true
          },
          "tooltip": { "mode": "multi", "sort": "desc" }
        },
        "targets": [
          {
            "datasource": "$datasource",
            "editorMode": "code",
            "expr": "max by (image_tag) (tuist_kura_fleet_servers{env=\"$env\"})",
            "legendFormat": "{{image_tag}}",
            "refId": "A"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Servers per observed image tag",
        "type": "timeseries"
      },
      {
        "collapsed": false,
        "gridPos": { "h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 19 },
        "id": 300,
        "panels": [],
        "title": "Gate signals (per node)",
        "type": "row"
      },
      {
        "datasource": "$datasource",
        "description": "Replication outbox depth per pod. The gate allows 10% growth over the pre-upgrade baseline (with a small absolute floor); unbounded growth after an upgrade is the classic degraded-but-up regression.",
        "fieldConfig": {
          "defaults": {
            "color": { "mode": "palette-classic" },
            "custom": {
              "drawStyle": "line",
              "fillOpacity": 10,
              "lineWidth": 1,
              "showPoints": "never"
            },
            "unit": "short"
          }
        },
        "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 20 },
        "id": 310,
        "options": {
          "legend": {
            "displayMode": "list",
            "placement": "bottom",
            "showLegend": true
          },
          "tooltip": { "mode": "multi", "sort": "desc" }
        },
        "targets": [
          {
            "datasource": "$datasource",
            "editorMode": "code",
            "expr": "sum by (pod) (kura_outbox_messages{cluster=~\"tuist-$env\"})",
            "legendFormat": "{{pod}}",
            "refId": "A"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Outbox depth",
        "type": "timeseries"
      },
      {
        "datasource": "$datasource",
        "description": "File-descriptor wait timeouts per pod (fd-pool pressure). The gate pauses on any growth over the pre-upgrade baseline.",
        "fieldConfig": {
          "defaults": {
            "color": { "mode": "palette-classic" },
            "custom": {
              "drawStyle": "line",
              "fillOpacity": 10,
              "lineWidth": 1,
              "showPoints": "never"
            },
            "unit": "ops"
          }
        },
        "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 20 },
        "id": 311,
        "options": {
          "legend": {
            "displayMode": "list",
            "placement": "bottom",
            "showLegend": true
          },
          "tooltip": { "mode": "multi", "sort": "desc" }
        },
        "targets": [
          {
            "datasource": "$datasource",
            "editorMode": "code",
            "expr": "sum by (pod) (rate(kura_file_descriptor_wait_seconds_count{result=\"timeout\", cluster=~\"tuist-$env\"}[5m]))",
            "legendFormat": "{{pod}}",
            "refId": "A"
          }
        ],
        "title": "FD wait timeouts",
        "type": "timeseries"
      },
      {
        "datasource": "$datasource",
        "description": "Peer-plane request failures per pod: outbox replication deliveries and bootstrap runs that errored against a peer. The gate pauses on any growth over the pre-upgrade baseline.",
        "fieldConfig": {
          "defaults": {
            "color": { "mode": "palette-classic" },
            "custom": {
              "drawStyle": "line",
              "fillOpacity": 10,
              "lineWidth": 1,
              "showPoints": "never"
            },
            "unit": "ops"
          }
        },
        "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 28 },
        "id": 312,
        "options": {
          "legend": {
            "displayMode": "list",
            "placement": "bottom",
            "showLegend": true
          },
          "tooltip": { "mode": "multi", "sort": "desc" }
        },
        "targets": [
          {
            "datasource": "$datasource",
            "editorMode": "code",
            "expr": "sum by (pod) (rate(kura_peer_connection_failures_total{cluster=~\"tuist-$env\"}[5m]))",
            "legendFormat": "{{pod}}",
            "refId": "A"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Peer connection failures",
        "type": "timeseries"
      },
      {
        "datasource": "$datasource",
        "description": "Memory pressure state per pod (0 normal, 1 soft, 2 critical). Critical pressure on an updated server pauses the rollout immediately.",
        "fieldConfig": {
          "defaults": {
            "color": { "mode": "thresholds" },
            "custom": {
              "drawStyle": "line",
              "fillOpacity": 10,
              "lineWidth": 1,
              "showPoints": "never"
            },
            "max": 2,
            "min": 0,
            "thresholds": {
              "mode": "absolute",
              "steps": [
                { "color": "green", "value": null },
                { "color": "yellow", "value": 1 },
                { "color": "red", "value": 2 }
              ]
            },
            "unit": "short"
          }
        },
        "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 28 },
        "id": 313,
        "options": {
          "legend": {
            "displayMode": "list",
            "placement": "bottom",
            "showLegend": true
          },
          "tooltip": { "mode": "multi", "sort": "desc" }
        },
        "targets": [
          {
            "datasource": "$datasource",
            "editorMode": "code",
            "expr": "max by (pod) (kura_memory_pressure_state{cluster=~\"tuist-$env\"})",
            "legendFormat": "{{pod}}",
            "refId": "A"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Memory pressure",
        "type": "timeseries"
      },
      {
        "collapsed": false,
        "gridPos": { "h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 36 },
        "id": 400,
        "panels": [],
        "title": "Alerting",
        "type": "row"
      },
      {
        "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 37 },
        "id": 410,
        "options": {
          "code": { "language": "plaintext", "showLineNumbers": false, "showMiniMap": false },
          "content": "Grafana is the paging authority for rollouts — the reconciler cannot report its own death. Provision these rules in Grafana Cloud alerting, routed through the production IRM escalation:\n\n1. **Rollout paused, sustained (page).** `max(tuist_kura_rollout_paused{env=\"production\"}) == 1` for 5m. The `image_tag` and wave come from `tuist_kura_rollout_paused` / `tuist_kura_rollout_wave` labels; link this dashboard in the annotation.\n2. **Rollout active too long (warn).** `max(tuist_kura_rollout_active{env=\"production\"}) == 1` for 4h. Also covers the forgotten pause, since a paused rollout stays active.\n3. **Rollout metrics absent while recently active (page).** `(max by (env) (max_over_time(tuist_kura_rollout_active{env=\"production\"}[2h]))) unless (max by (env) (tuist_kura_rollout_active{env=\"production\"}))` for 5m — the series existed within the window but is gone now, which is what a control plane dying mid-rollout looks like. Both sides MUST aggregate to the stable `env` label before `unless`: the raw series carries pod/instance scrape labels, so an ordinary server pod replacement would otherwise leave an old label set in the range window with no current match and page on routine churn. The `rollout_active` gauge is emitted every poll (0 when idle) precisely so absence is meaningful.",
          "mode": "markdown"
        },
        "pluginVersion": "11.4.0",
        "targets": [],
        "title": "Alert rules (provisioned in Grafana Cloud)",
        "type": "text"
      }
    ]
  }
}
